市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Railway Shrine (Oita)|qq=}} – Shrine located on the rooftop of {{ill|JR Ōita City|ja|JRおおいたシティ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/JR Ōita City|qq=}} at Ōita Station in Ōita City, Ōita Prefecture. * Japan Railway Shrine – Shrine located within the [[:en:Museum Yamato Bunkakan|Yamato Bunkakan]] in Nara City, Nara Prefecture. Adjacent to Nihon Railway Reisha and Iwafune Inari Shrine.<ref>『近畿日本鉄道100th year のあゆみ』p.572 2010th year 近畿日本鉄道</ref> * {{ill|Aizu Railway Shrine|ja|会津鉄道神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Aizu Railway Shrine|qq=}} – Shrine located in front of Ashinomaki-Onsen Station in Aizuwakamatsu City, Fukushima Prefecture. * {{ill|Shinano Railway Shrine|ja|しなの鉄道神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinano Railway Shrine|qq=}} – Shrine located within Karuizawa Station in Karuizawa Town, Kitasaku District, Nagano Prefecture. * {{ill|Shinshimashima Station Railway Shrine|ja|新島々駅鉄道神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinshimashima Station Railway Shrine|qq=}} – Shrine located within Shinshimashima Station in Matsumoto City, Nagano Prefecture. * {{ill|Hitachinaka Kaiun Railway Shrine|ja|ひたちなか開運鉄道神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hitachinaka Kaiun Railway Shrine|qq=}} – Shrine located within Ajigaura Station in Hitachinaka City, Ibaraki Prefecture.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://ibarakinews.jp/news/newsdetail.php?f_jun=16241069152866|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210620010818/https://ibarakinews.jp/news/newsdetail.php?f_jun=16241069152866|title=「キハ222」がご神体 「鉄道神社」誕生祝う レール製鳥居も|newspaper=茨城新聞|date=2021-06-20|accessdate=2021-06-20|archivedate=2021-06-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://nordot.app/778873326079115264|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210620013558/https://nordot.app/778873326079115264|title=引退車両をご神体に鉄道神社建立 茨城、交通安全御利益PR|newspaper=共同通信|date=2021-06-19|accessdate=2021-06-20|archivedate=2021-06-20}}</ref>
== Shrines closely associated with railways == * {{ill|Kumanodaira Shrine|ja|熊ノ平神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumanodaira Shrine|qq=}} – Shrine at former Kumanodaira Station, JR Ichinomiya. * {{ill|Tanna Shrine|ja|丹那神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tanna Shrine|qq=}} – Shrine honoring those who died constructing the Tanna Tunnel. * {{ill|Shutetsu Shrine|ja|守鐡社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shutetsu Shrine|qq=}} – Shrine dedicated to railway protection in front of Mooka Station. * {{ill|Senmori Inari Shrine|ja|線守稲荷神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senmori Inari Shrine|qq=}} * {{ill|Torigoe Inari Shrine|ja|鳥越稲荷神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Torigoe Inari Shrine|qq=}} – Shrine located within Shimonoe Station. * {{ill|Kayashima Shrine|ja|萱島神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kayashima Shrine|qq=}} – Shrine located under Kayashima Station in Neyagawa City, Osaka Prefecture. Revived by Keihan Electric Railway during station expansion. * Transportation Shrine – Shrine located within {{ill|Amu Plaza Miyazaki|ja|アミュプラザみやざき|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amu Plaza Miyazaki|qq=}} in Miyazaki City, Miyazaki Prefecture.
